The paper investigates the commit behavior of software developers in open-source software projects, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The paper also analyzes the statistical distribution of commit intervals, which could be relevant to the sub-categories of social and information networks (cs.SI) and systems and control (cs.SD). Additionally, the paper focuses on the dynamics of open-source software development, which could be relevant to the programming languages (cs.PL) and computers and society (cs.CY) sub-categories.
